Label: Create Property
Description: This flow helps agents creating new properties in just a few clicks. It calculates the geocoded address calling out to a 3rd party service.

Label: Basic Approval Request
Description: Allows a content author to submit a content variant for content manager review, and allows for content variant revisions before the content manager approves for publication.

Label: CMS: Check Whether Any Step is Completed
Description: Determines whether either of two specified steps in a stage has completed.

Label: CMS: Notify Content Author
Description: Notifies the content author that their content variant has been approved, and allows the content author to conditionally view the final feedback for the content variant.

Label: CMS: Review Content
Description: Allows a content manager to conditionally view a content author's feedback, provide revision comments, and approve or request revisions of a content variant.

Label: CMS: Submit Content for Review
Description: Allows a content author to conditionally view a reviewer's feedback, provide revision comments, and submit a content variant for review.

Label: CMS: Withdraw Review Request
Description: Allows a content author to withdraw a review request in order to make changes to the underlying content variant.

Label: Chats Routed to Agents and Queues
Description: Routes each chat to an agent or queue based on conditions that you define.

Label: Chats Routed to Agents with the Right Skills
Description: Routes each chat to an agent with the required skills based on conditions that you define.

Label: Messages Routed to Agents and Queues
Description: Routes each message to an agent or queue based on conditions that you define.

Label: Voice Calls Routed to Agents and Queues
Description: Routes each call to an agent or queue based on conditions that you define.

Label: Voice Calls Routed to Basic Queue with Case Creation
Description: Routes each call to the default queue (Basic Queue) and, if the agent accepts, screen pops the new case for this call and identifies the caller.

Label: Add or Modify Service Appointment Attendees
Description: Add, modify, or delete a service appointment attendee record from a group service appointment.

Label: Create Waitlist
Description: Create a waitlist to manage drop-in customers for a service territory.

Label: Enroll or Unenroll Service Appointment Attendees
Description: Enrolls or unenrolls a service appointment attendee from a group service appointment.

Label: Book Appointment from Invitation
Description: Use an appointment invitation to book an appointment.

Label: Generate Appointment Invitation
Description: Creates an appointment invitation for internal or credentialed external users that can be shared with anyone.

Label: Modify Guest Service Appointment
Description: Modifies or cancels a service appointment for an unauthenticated user.

Label: Reassign Multiple Service Appointments
Description: Reassign multiple service appointments of an unavailable service resource to other available service resources.

Label: Send Appointment Invitation to Actionable List Members
Description: Creates an appointment invitation for internal and credentialed external users, and sends that invitation to the selected members of the actionable list.

Label: Cancel Item Flow
Description: Order Management: Cancel order items before fulfillment.

Label: Create Order Summary Flow
Description: Order Management: Create an Order Summary record from an order.

Label: Create Process Exception Flow
Description: Create a process exception record from a process exception event.

Label: Return Item Flow
Description: Order Management: Return order items after fulfillment.

Label: Recurrence Schedule Flow
Description: Flow for creating object items from Recurrence Scheduler Records

Label: Change Case Owner to Incident Owner
Description: When Cases are identified as part of an Incident, change the Case owner to the Incident owner.

Label: Close Change Request & Related Issues
Description: Closes a Change Request and attempts to close its related Incidents, Problems, and Cases.

Label: Find Contact Associated with Messaging Session
Description: Gets a contact record associated with the messaging user from a specified messaging session.

Label: Deploy Data Kit Component
Description: The flow deploys DataKit components in a sequential manner. It iterates through each DataKit component, deploying them one by one, and waits for a deployment event to check the status before moving on to the next component. This flow utilizes a DataKit deployment invocable action and a DataKit deployment event.

Label: Field Service Mobile: Create Leads and Opportunities
Description: Lets a flow user indicate customer interest in an upsell opportunity and creates any necessary lead and opportunity records.
